  "text": "The API server authentication implementation centers on `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go` which contains `Config.New()` \u2014 the authenticator chain constructor. It builds a union chain (via `request/union/union.go`) of: (1) x509 client certificate authenticator (`request/x509/x509.go`), (2) bearer token authenticator (`request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go`) wrapping a token union of service account authenticators (`pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go` for JWT validation, `claims.go` for bound token claims, `legacy.go` for legacy secret-based tokens), and (3) the anonymous authenticator (`request/anonymous/anonymous.go`) as a fallback. The `authenticator/interfaces.go` file defines the core `Token` and `Request` interfaces used throughout.",
